ription then results in a description of the matrix\nspace $\\mathbb{R}^{n \\times m}$, seen as the union of manifolds\n$\\mathcal{M}_r(\\mathbb{R}^{n \\times m})$, as an analytic manifold equipped with\na topology for which the matrix rank is a continuous map.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 May 2017 09:51:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-25"}
